Two women killed in mishap in Gaya 
19-1-2017 
At least two women including a Jain Sadhvi were killed and four others injured on Thursday when a speeding truck hit them in Biharâ€™s Gaya district, a police officer said. The incident occured in Ghodpari village near GT Road. The truck hit some Jain followers who were carting the differently-abled Sadhvi in a tricycle, Deputy Inspector General of Police (DIG) (Gaya Range), Saurabh Kumar said. The Sadhvi and her attendant died on the spot, while four others sustained injuries, he said.

